Bunaeopsis phidias is a moth of the  family Saturniidae. It is known from Africa, including Tanzania, Eritrea, Malawi and Zambia.The body of the male of this species has a length of 37 millimetres (1.5 in), its forewings 64 mm (2.5 in) and it has a wingspan of 112 mm (4.4 in). The ground colour of the forewings is a yellowish brown.